ood-thoughts-about-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":25459,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Dhikr: If he comes to Me walking, I come running","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 7, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace be and blessings on him, said, \"Allah Almighty says: I am as My servant expects of Me and I am with him as he remembers Me. If he remembers Me in himself, I will remember him in Myself. If he mentions Me\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3795,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/24\/accidentally-break-fast-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":25459,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: One who accidentally breaks fast completes it","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 24, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever eats or drinks forgetfully while he is fasting, let him complete his fast, for Allah has fed him and given him drink.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1933, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1155 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":13717,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/04\/24\/eat-drink-right-hand\/","url_meta":{"origin":25459,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Manners: Eating and drinking with right hand","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 24, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen one of you eats, let him eat with his right hand. When he drinks, let him drink with his right hand. Verily, the devil eats and drinks with his left hand.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2020\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":38214,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/09\/08\/ibn-masud-husn-al-thann\/","url_meta":{"origin":25459,"position":3},"title":"Ibn Mas\u2019ud on Optimism: Best virtue to have good assumptions about Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 8, 2022","format":false,"excerpt":"Khaythamah reported: Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cBy the One besides whom there is no God, a believing servant is not given anything better than good thoughts about Allah Almighty. By the One besides whom there is no God, a servant does not improve his\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6063,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/08\/brotherhood-assume-good-excuses\/","url_meta":{"origin":25459,"position":4},"title":"Umar on Brothers: Assume good from your brother, give excuses","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 8, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abi Mulaykah reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cIt is not allowed for a Muslim who hears a word from his brother to assume evil of him if he can find something good about it.\u201d Source: al-Tamhi\u0304d 18\/20 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0645\u064f\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0643\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":640,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/03\/19\/be-determined-in-your-dua\/","url_meta":{"origin":25459,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Dua: Be determined, certain in your supplications","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 19, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said,\u00a0\u201cWhen one of you calls upon Allah, let him be determined in the supplication and he should not say, 'O Allah, give me if You will,' for there is no one to coerce Allah.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25459","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadit